x\in R
x > 0
x^4+1 \geq x^3+x
x^4-x^3-x+1 \geq 1
x>1
 \frac 1x < 1\\ x<x^4\\ x + x^3 = 1\cdot x + \frac 1x \cdot x^4 \le \frac 1x \cdot x + 1\cdot x^4 = 1+x^4 
 \frac 1x \ge 1\\ x\ge x^4\\ x + x^3 = 1\cdot x + \frac 1x \cdot x^4 \le \frac 1x \cdot x + 1\cdot x^4 = 1+x^4 
x^4 - x^3 - x + 1 = x^3(x - 1) - (x - 1) = (x^3 -1)(x-1) = (x-1)^2 (x^2 + x + 1)
x\in \mathbb{R}
x>0
x^3-1=(x-1)(x^2+x+1)
x^4-x^3-x+1. 
x^4-x^3-x+1=x^3(x-1)-1(x-1)=(x-1)(x^3-1) 
x^4-x^3-x+1=(x-1)(x-1)(x^2+x+1) =(x-1)^2(x^2+x+1).
(x-1)^2(x^2+x+1)\geq 0
x>0
x=1>0
x^4-x^3-x+1\geq 0
x^4+1\geq x^3+x
x^4 - x^3 - x +1 = (x-1)(x^3 -1) =  (x-1)(x-1)(x^2+x+1) = (x-1)^2(x^2+x+1).
x
\forall x \in \mathbb{R}
